@@FindFilesDlg
<TITLE FindFilesDlg function>
Summary
  Displays Windows' built-in search files dialog.
Description
  Call FindFilesDlg to access the file search functionality built into Windows Explorer. If you are
  running Windows 95, 98 or NT, this function displays a dialog. If you are using Windows 2000 or XP,
  this function displays a search panel inside Windows Explorer.

  This function is a wrapper for the TJvFindFilesDialog component so you don't need to create an
  instance of the component at run-time.
Parameters
  StartIn       - The start folder if the folder is a file system directory.
  SpecialFolder - The start folder if the folder is one of the special folders available in Windows.
  UseFolder     - Controls whether StartIn or SpecialFolder is used. Set to true to use SpecialFolder,
                   to false to use Directory.
See Also
  TJvFindFilesDialog

